id: pm-vjk3
title: "Bare-core audit extraction phase 2: move audit command implementations and audit flags out of default CLI/SDK into pm-governance-audit"
description: "User directive 2026-07-12: default pm CLI and public SDK must not include ANY audit commands or flags; all audit surface lives in the first-party audit plugin. EXTEND packages/pm-governance-audit (packages-first rule) — do NOT create a parallel pm-audit package; optionally add an 'audit' package alias. Phase 1 (closed pm-ixt3) moved registration only — implementations, SDK exports, and all audit flags are still core. Full inventory, scope fence, mechanisms, decisions, and slice order in body."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: bare-core,cli,governance,packages,refactor,sdk
created_at: "2026-07-12T19:53:05.226Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-12T19:56:05.126Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 60
acceptance_criteria: "src/cli/commands/{dedupe-audit,dedupe-merge,comments-audit,normalize}.ts no longer exist in core src; implementations live in packages/pm-governance-audit; runDedupeAudit/runCommentsAudit/runDedupeMerge/runNormalize removed from public SDK exports (sdk/index.ts, sdk/runtime.ts); bare-core pm --help, completion, contracts, and MCP tool definitions contain no --audit or --allow-audit-* surface; installed pm-governance-audit restores every removed command and flag with identical behavior; coverage gate, contracts:update, tool-count assertions, docs, and token-surface baseline all reconciled"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: medium
