body: "# Bare-core audit extraction — phase 2 program plan (filed 2026-07-12, directed pass)\n\n## Goal (user directive)\nDefault `pm` CLI and public SDK must not include ANY audit commands or audit flags. All audit surface lives in the separate first-party audit plugin. Target package = existing `packages/pm-governance-audit` (packages-first: EXTEND, never create a parallel pm-audit package). Optionally add an `audit` alias to its `pm.aliases` so `pm install audit` works — record under D1.\n\n## Current state (verified 2026-07-12 on main @ d9507407)\nPhase 1 (closed pm-ixt3, parent pm-59gj) extracted command REGISTRATION only: bare core no longer registers `dedupe-audit` / `dedupe-merge` / `comments-audit` / `normalize`; the package registers them but its runtime (packages/pm-governance-audit/extensions/governance-audit/runtime.ts, `loadGovernanceModule` via PM_CLI_PACKAGE_ROOT) dynamically imports the implementations FROM core SDK at run time.\n\nStill shipping in default core:\n1. **Implementations (~2,146 LOC)**: src/cli/commands/dedupe-audit.ts (639), dedupe-merge.ts (486), comments-audit.ts (460), normalize.ts (561) — bundled with every CLI install.\n2. **Public SDK exports**: src/sdk/index.ts:276–281 and src/sdk/runtime.ts:429–453 export runDedupeAudit / runCommentsAudit / runDedupeMerge / runNormalize.\n3. **Core-registered CLI flags**:\n   - `--audit` on `pm files` and `pm docs` (src/cli/register-mutation.ts ~3163 and ~3221) — cross-item linked-path usage report mode handled inside runFilesAction / runDocsAction.\n   - `--allow-audit-update`, `--allow-audit-dep-update` on `pm update` / `update-many` (src/cli/registration-helpers.ts:527–532 anyOptionTrue merge; src/cli/commands/update-many.ts:59–60; normalize passthrough src/cli/commands/normalize.ts:96/494/501).\n   - `--allow-audit-comment` (src/cli/commands/comments.ts:41), `--allow-audit-note` + `--allow-audit-comment` (notes), `--allow-audit-learning` + `--allow-audit-comment` (src/cli/commands/learnings.ts:33–35) — merged into `allowAuditBypass` (register-mutation.ts:1376/1671/1714).\n   - `--allow-audit-release` (src/cli/register-operations.ts:573).\n4. **SDK contracts**: src/sdk/cli-contracts/flag-contracts.ts — dedupe/comments audit flag tables (~256/~286), `--audit` entries (~352/~368), allow-audit-* entries (~314–336, ~809, ~1203–1348); tool-option-contracts.ts:285–286 (camelCase MCP param mappings); tool-parameter-tables.ts; tool-schema.ts.\n5. **MCP**: src/mcp/tool-definitions.ts:392 — pm_files description advertises the audit mode; allowAudit* params flow through the shared option contracts; pm_run doc line ~58 already frames dedupe-audit/comments-audit/normalize as dynamic package-owned actions (that is the correct end state — keep).\n6. **Presentation/UX**: help-content.ts, error-guidance.ts:703 (ownership-conflict guidance names the audit flags), core/diagnostics/remediation.ts, shell completion (bash+zsh+fish), docs/ (12 files mention audit), core/profile/profile-presets.ts, core/telemetry/observability.ts.\n\n## Scope fence\n- **IN**: the four command implementations + their SDK exports; the `--audit` files/docs report mode; the six `--allow-audit-*` flags; every contract/MCP/completion/help/docs entry for those.\n- **OUT (stays core)**: the audit-protection ENFORCEMENT itself (ownership/audit guard in core store + governance issue codes + the error-guidance path for ownership conflicts); history-redact / history-compact / history-repair (\"audited history stream\" is a different sense of the word); `pm validate` checks; the package's existing onRead/onWrite hook log.\n\n## Mechanisms (verified in source)\n- `ExtensionApi.registerFlags(targetCommand, FlagDefinition[])` (core/extensions/extension-types.ts:1363) — plugin-owned flags on existing core commands; parsed via the extensionFlagDefinitions plumbing in cli/main.ts (~:948–:1133). Core option reads are generic (anyOptionTrue with alias lists), so core enforcement can keep honoring allowAudit* option VALUES while the plugin owns registration/help/completion.\n- `ExtensionApi.registerCommand(command, override)` — plugin may override `pm files` / `pm docs` to add the --audit report mode, or ship the report as a package-owned command.\n- Package code is TypeScript-only (.ts entries, native type-stripping loader — pm-2p7a); installed npm extensions untracked in git (pm-sod3).\n\n## Decisions needed BEFORE S2/S3 (see Decision child)\n- **D1**: handling mechanism for plugin-owned flags on core commands — registerFlags + registerCommand override vs package-owned subcommands; plus whether to add the `audit` package alias.\n- **D2**: bare-core behavior when the plugin is absent — do non-owner audit-gated mutations fall back to `--force` only, or hard-block? Does the SDK keep a *programmatic* allowAuditBypass option (not a CLI flag), and what is the breaking-change posture for deleting the four SDK exports (older published package versions dynamic-import them; first-party is covered by same-cut date-based lockstep + pm_min_version bump, but external SDK consumers lose the exports)?\n\n## Sequencing & risks\n- pm-qfdd (commander program singleton leaks dynamic extension flags across in-process invocations) — affects in-process tests of plugin-registered flags; prefer worker-bridge suites (pm-kvd0 pattern); coordinate if qfdd still open at implementation time.\n- pm-kb5h / pm-yh8r fences: files move WITH their owning slice — these four files leave src/ under THIS program; cite pm-vjk3, not kb5h.\n- Coverage: 100% literal all-src gate loses ~2,146 LOC from src/; the package needs equivalent spec coverage; vitest.config + `pnpm contracts:update` + the tool-count assertion in 4 places all need reconciliation.\n- Token-surface win expected (help + MCP tools/list shrink): re-measure with scripts/measure-agent-token-surface.mjs and record on the pm-mpbb ledger.\n- Release coordination: package pm_min_version bump in the same daily cut (date-based lockstep, scripts/sync-versions.mjs).\n\n## Slice order (children)\nS1 relocate implementations + drop SDK exports (no decision dependency — start here) → D1/D2 decision → S2 `--audit` files/docs mode → S3 `--allow-audit-*` family → S4 contracts/MCP/help/docs purge + token re-measure → S5 coverage + bare-vs-installed e2e verification.\n\n## Entry point for next session\nRead this body + children top-down. D1/D2 are maintainer decisions (decision_needed queue). S1 is actionable immediately."
